s visualized posterior to fibroglandular tissues","definition":"Image quality deficiency according to MQCM"},{"code":"111199","display":"MLO Poor separation of deep and superficial breast tissues","definition":"Image quality deficiency according to MQCM"},{"code":"111200","display":"MLO Evidence of motion blur","definition":"Image quality deficiency according to MQCM"},{"code":"111201","display":"MLO Inframammary fold is not open","definition":"Image quality deficiency according to MQCM"},{"code":"111202","display":"CC Not all medial tissue visualized","definition":"Image quality deficiency according to MQCM"},{"code":"111203","display":"CC Nipple not centered on image","definition":"Image quality deficiency according to MQCM"},{"code":"111204","display":"CC Posterior nipple line does not measure within 1 cm of MLO","definition":"Image quality deficiency according to MQCM"},{"code":"111205","display":"Nipple not in profile","definition":"Image quality deficiency"},{"code":"111206","display":"Insufficient implant displacement incorrect","definition":"Image quality deficiency according to MQCM"},{"code":"111207","display":"Image artifact(s)","definition":"Signals that do not faithfully reproduce actual anatomic structures because of distortion or of addition or deletion of information"},{"code":"111208","display":"Grid artifact(s)","definition":"Feature(s) arising from the acquisition unit's anti-scatter grid mechanism. For two-dimensional systems, such features include those of mechanically damaged or incorrectly positioned grids. For moving or Bucky grids, artifacts may result from intentional grid motion that is inadequate in duration or velocity uniformity"},{"code":"111209","display":"Positioning","definition":"Inadequate arrangement of the anatomy of interest with respect to the X-Ray field and image detector sensitive area. Examples: 1) positioning is \"cutoff\" when the projection of anatomy of interest falls outside the sensitive area of the detector; 2) \"cone cut\", in which the X-Ray field does not adequately cover the anatomy of interest; 3) detector's sensitive surface is too small to cover the projection of the anatomy of interest; 4) improper angular orientation or \"rotation\" of anatomy of interest with respect to the X-Ray source, or detector; 5) projection of other anatomy or clothing over the anatomy of interest in the image"},{"code":"111210","display":"Motion blur","definition":"Unacceptable image blur resulting from motion of the anatomy of interest during exposure or the inadequately compensated motion of X-Ray source with respect to the image detector during exposure"},{"code":"111211","display":"Under exposed","definition":"Inadequate number of quanta reached the detector during exposure. Reasons for under exposed images include low kVp, low mAs product, excess Source Image Distance. Under exposed images have inadequate signal and higher noise in the areas of interest"},{"code":"111212","display":"Over exposed","definition":"An excess number of quanta reached the detector during exposure. Reasons for over exposed images include high kVp, high mAs product, short Source Image Distance. Over exposed images have high signal and lower noise in the areas of interest. Over exposed area may demonstrate lack of contrast from over saturation of the detector"},{"code":"111213","display":"No image","definition":"No evidence of a patient exposure"},{"code":"111214","display":"Detector artifact(s)","definition":"Superposed features or flaws of the detector"},{"code":"111215","display":"Artifact(s) other than grid or detector artifact","definition":"Features or discontinuities arising from causes other than the anti-scatter grid and image detector"},{"code":"111216","display":"Mechanical failure","definition":"Failure of the device to operate according to mechanical design specifications"},{"code":"111217","display":"Electrical failure","definition":"Failure of a device to operate according to electrical design specifications"},{"code":"111218","display":"Software failure","definition":"Attributable to software used in generation or handling of image"},{"code":"111219","display":"Inappropriate image processing","definition":"Images processed inappropriately, not following appropriate protocol"},{"code":"111220","display":"Other failure","definition":"Failure that is not mechanical or electrical or otherwise described"},{"code":"111221","display":"Unknown failure","definition":"Unidentified or unknown cause of failure"},{"code":"111222","display":"Succeeded","definition":"The attempted process was completely successful"},{"code":"111223","display":"Partially Succeeded","definition":"The attempted process succeeded in some ways, but failed in others"},{"code":"111224","display":"Failed","definition":"The attempted process completely failed"},{"code":"111225","display":"Not Attempted","definition":"No process was performed"},{"code":"111233","display":"Individual Impression / Recommendation Analysis","definition":"Analysis of a related group of findings or features detected during image data inspection, to produce a summary impression and/or recommendation"},{"code":"111234","display":"Overall Impression / Recommendation Analysis","definition":"Analysis of all groups of findings or features, to produce a single impression and/or recommendation"},{"code":"111235","display":"Unusable - Quality renders image unusable","definition":"The usability of an image for diagnostic interpretation or CAD, based on a quality control standard"},{"code":"111236","display":"Usable - Does not meet the quality control standard","definition":"The usability of an image for diagnostic interpretation or CAD, based on a quality control standard"},{"code":"111237","display":"Usable - Meets the quality control standard","definition":"The usability of an image for diagnostic interpretation or CAD, based on a quality control standard"},{"code":"111238","display":"Mammography Quality Control Manual 1999, ACR","definition":"An image quality control standard specified by the American College of Radiology"},{"code":"111239","display":"Title 21 CFR Section 900, Subpart B","definition":"An image quality control standard in the US Code of Federal Regulations"},{"code":"111240","display":"Institutionally defined quality control standard","definition":"An image quality control standard specified or adopted by the institution responsible for the document"},{"code":"111241","display":"All algorithms succeeded; without findings","definition":"No findings resulted upon successful completion of all attempted computer-aided detection and/or analysis"},{"code":"111242","display":"All algorithms succeeded; with findings","definition":"One or more findings resulted upon successful completion of all attempted computer-aided detection and/or analysis"},{"code":"111243","display":"Not all algorithms succeeded; without findings","definition":"No findings resulted from the attempted computer-aided detection and/or analysis, but one or more failures occurred in the process"},{"code":"111244","display":"Not all algorithms succeeded; with findings","definition":"One or more findings resulted from the attempted computer-aided detection and/or analysis, but one or more failures occurred in the process"},{"code":"111245","display":"No algorithms succeeded; without findings","definition":"All of the attempted computer-aided detection and/or analysis failed, so there could be no findings"},{"extension":[{"url":"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/codesystem-replacedby","valueCoding":{"system":"http://hl7.org/fhir/sid/srt","code":"M-83240","display":"Adenolipoma"}}],"code":"111248","display":"Adenolipoma","definition":"A benign tumor having glandular characteristics but composed of fat, with the presence of normal mammary ducts","property":[{"code":"status","valueCode":"deprecated"}]},{"extension":[{"url":"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/codesystem-replacedby","valueCoding":{"system":"http://hl7.org/fhir/sid/srt","code":"M-72170","display":"Ductal hyperplasia, Usual"}}],"code":"111249","display":"Ductal hyperplasia","definition":"Hyperplasia is also known as epithelial hyperplasia or proliferative breast disease. It's an overgrowth of the cells that line the ducts or the lobules. Based on how the cells look under a microscope, the hyperplasia is called either ductal hyperplasia (also called duct epithelial hyperplasia) or lobular hyperplasia. Based on the pattern of the cells, hyperplasia may be called usual or atypical. In usual hyperplasia, the pattern of cells is very close to normal. Atypical hyperplasia (or hyperplasia with atypia) is a term used when the cells are more distorted. FROM: http://www.cancer.org/healthy/findcancerearly/womenshealth/non-cancerousbreastconditions/non-cancerous-breast-conditions-hyperplasia","property":[{"code":"status","valueCode":"deprecated"}]},{"extension":[{"url":"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/codesystem-replacedby","valueCoding":{"system":"http://hl7.org/fhir/sid/srt","code":"M-89830","display":"Adenomyoepithelioma"}}],"code":"111250","display":"Adenomyoepithelioma","definition":"Neoplasms composed of myoepithelial cells","property":[{"code":"status","valueCode":"deprecated"}]},{"code":"111251","display":"Normal axillary node","definition":"Axillary node that is normal in appearance with no associated pathology"},{"code":"111252","display":"Axillary node with calcifications","definition":"Axillary node containing calcifications"},{"code":"111253","display":"Axillary node hyperplasia","definition":"Excessive proliferation of normal tissue arrangement of the axillary node"},{"extension":[{"url":"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/codesystem-replacedby","valueCoding":{"system":"http://hl7.org/fhir/sid/srt","code":"F-8A063","display":"Asynchronous involution of breast"}}],"code":"111254","display":"Asynchronous involution","property":[{"code":"status","valueCode":"deprecated"}]},{"code":"111255","display":"Benign cyst with blood","definition":"Cyst with benign morphology containing blood"},{"code":"111256","display":"Benign Calcifications","definition":"Calcifications having typically benign morphology. They are not of intermediate or high probability of concern for malignancy"},{"extension":[{"url":"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/codesystem-replacedby","valueCoding":{"system":"http://hl7.org/fhir/sid/srt","code":"M-85040","display":"Intracystic papilloma"}}],"code":"111257","display":"Intracystic papilloma","definition":"Growing within a cystic adenoma, filling the cavity with a mass of branching epithelial processes","property":[{"code":"status","valueCode":"deprecated"}]},{"code":"111258","display":"Ductal adenoma","definition":"Adenoma located in mammary duct, present as discrete sclerotic nodules, solitary or multiple"},{"code":"111259","display":"Diabetic fibrous mastopathy","definition":"The occurrence of fibrous tumor-forming stromal proliferation in patients with diabetes mellitus"},{"extension":[{"url":"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/codesystem-replacedby","valueCoding":{"system":"http://hl7.org/fhir/sid/srt","code":"M-88211","display":"Extra abdominal desmoid"}}],"code":"111260","display":"Extra abdominal desmoid","definition":"A deep seated firm tumor frequently occurring on the chest consisting of collagenous tissue that infiltrates surround muscle; frequently recurs but does not metastasize","property":[{"code":"status","valueCode":"deprecated"}]},{"extension":[{"url":"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/codesystem-replacedby","valueCoding":{"system":"http://hl7.org/fhir/sid/srt","code":"M-33410","display":"Epidermal inclusion cyst"}}],"code":"111262","display":"Epidermal inclusion cyst","definition":"A cyst formed of a mass of epithelial cells, as a result of trauma has been pushed beneath the epidermis. The cyst is lined with squamous epithelium and contains concentric layers or keratin","property":[{"code":"status","valueCode":"deprecated"}]},{"code":"111263","display":"Fibroadenomatoid hyperplasia","definition":"Excessive proliferation of fibroadenoma tissue"},{"code":"111264","display":"Fibroadenolipoma","definition":"A lipoma with an abundant stroma of fibrous tissue"},{"extension":[{"url":"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/codesystem-replacedby","valueCoding":{"system":"http://hl7.org/fhir/sid/srt","code":"M-44140","display":"Foreign body (reaction"}}],"code":"111265","display":"Foreign body (reaction)","property":[{"code":"status","valueCode":"deprecated"}]},{"extension":[{"url":"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/codesystem-replacedby","valueCoding":{"system":"http://hl7.org/fhir/sid/srt","code":"D7-90364","display":"Galactocele"}}],"code":"111269","display":"Galactocele","definition":"Retention cyst caused by occlusion of a lactiferous duct","property":[{"code":"status","valueCode":"deprecated"}]},{"extension":[{"url":"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/codesystem-replacedby","valueCoding":{"system":"http://hl7.org/fhir/sid/srt","code":"D3-F0620","display":"Hemangioma of subcutaneous tissue"}}],"code":"111271","display":"Hemangioma - nonparenchymal, subcutaneous","definition":"A congenital anomaly that leads to a proliferation of blood vessels leading to a mass that resembles a neoplasm, not located in parenchymal areas but subcutaneous","property":[{"code":"status","valueCode":"deprecated"}]},{"extension":[{"url":"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/codesystem-replacedby","valueCoding":{"system":"http://hl7.org/fhir/sid/srt","code":"M-72000","display":"Hyperplasia, usual"}}],"code":"111273","display":"Hyperplasia, usual","definition":"Hyperplasia is also known as epithelial hyperplasia or proliferative breast disease. It's an overgrowth of the cells that line the ducts or the lobules. Based on how the cells look under a microscope, the hyperplasia is called either ductal hyperplasia (also called duct epithelial hyperplasia) or lobular hyperplasia. FROM: http://www.cancer.org/healthy/findcancerearly/womenshealth/non-cancerousbreastconditions/non-cancerous-breast-conditions-hyperplasia","property":[{"code":"status","valueCode":"deprecated"}]},{"code":"111277","display":"Juvenile papillomatosis","definition":"A form of fibrocystic disease in young woman with florid and sclerosing adenosis that microscopically may suggest carcinoma"},{"extension":[{"url":"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/codesystem-replacedby","valueCoding":{"system":"http://hl7.org/fhir/sid/srt","code":"M-82040","display":"Lactating adenoma"}}],"code":"111278","display":"Lactating adenoma","definition":"Enlarging masses during lactation. A circumscribed benign tumor composed primarily of glandular structures with scanty stroma, with prominent secretory changes in the duct","property":[{"code":"status","valueCode":"deprecated"}]},{"code":"111279","display":"Lactational change","definition":"Changes related to the process of lactation"},{"code":"111281","display":"Large duct papilloma","definition":"A papilloma pertaining to large mammary duct"},{"extension":[{"url":"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/codesystem-replacedby","valueCoding":{"system":"http://hl7.org/fhir/sid/srt","code":"M-88250","display":"Myofibroblastoma"}}],"code":"111283","display":"Myofibroblastoma","definition":"Solitary or multiple tumors of muscles and fibrous tissues, or tumors composed of myofibroblasts","property":[{"code":"status","valueCode":"deprecated"}]},{"code":"111284","display":"Microglandular adenosis","definition":"Irregular clusters of small tubules are present in adipose or fibrous tissue, resembling tubular carcinoma but lacking stromal fibroblastic proliferation"},{"code":"111285","display":"Multiple Intraductal Papillomas","definition":"Papilloma typically involving an aggregate of adjacent ducts in the periphery of the breast, likely representing involvement of several foci of one or two duct systems"},{"code":"111286","display":"No abnormality","definition":"No abnormality"},{"code":"111287","display":"Normal breast tissue","definition":"Normal breast tissue"},{"extension":[{"url":"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/codesystem-replacedby","valueCoding":{"system":"http://hl7.org/fhir/sid/srt","code":"M-95401","display":"Neurofibromatosis"}}],"code":"111288","display":"Neurofibromatosis","definition":"Condition in which there are tumors of various sizes on peripheral nerves. They may be neuromas or fibromas","property":[{"code":"status","valueCode":"deprecated"}]},{"code":"111290","display":"Oil cyst (fat necrosis cyst)","definition":"A cyst resulting from the loss of the epithelial lining of a sebaceous dermoid or lacteal cyst"},{"code":"111291","display":"Post reduction mammoplasty","definition":"Breast tissue with characteristics of a benign nature, following breast reduction surgery"},{"code":"111292","display":"Pseudoangiomatous stromal hyperplasia","definition":"A benign stromal lesion composed of intermixed stromal and epithelial elements. The lobular and duct structures of the breast parenchyma are separated by an increased amount of stroma, non specific proliferative epithelial changes include hyperplasia of duct and lobular epithelium often with accentuation of myoepithelial cells and aprocine metaplasia with or without cyst formation"},{"extension":[{"url":"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/codesystem-replacedby","valueCoding":{"system":"http://hl7.org/fhir/sid/srt","code":"M-78731","display":"Radial scar"}}],"code":"111293","display":"Radial scar","definition":"An nonencapsulated stellate lesion consisting of a fibroelastic core and radiating bands of fibrous connective tissue containing lobules manifesting adenosis and ducts with papillary or diffuse intraductal hyperplasia","property":[{"code":"status","valueCode":"deprecated"}]},{"extension":[{"url":"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/codesystem-replacedby","valueCoding":{"system":"http://hl7.org/fhir/sid/srt","code":"M-74220","display":"Sclerosing adenosis"}}],"code":"111294","display":"Sclerosing adenosis","definition":"Prominent interductal fibrosis of the terminal ductules","property":[{"code":"status","valueCode":"deprecated"}]},{"code":"111296","display":"Silicone granuloma","definition":"Nodular inflammatory lesions due to the presence of silicone in the breast tissue"},{"code":"111297","display":"Nipple Characteristic","definition":"The morphologic status of the nipple"},{"code":"111298","display":"Virginal hyperplasia","definition":"Spontaneous excessive proliferation of breast tissue, usually found in younger women"},{"code":"111299","display":"Peripheral duct papillomas","definition":"Papilloma(s) pertaining the peripheral ducts"},{"code":"111300","display":"Axillary node with lymphoma","definition":"Axillary node with lymphoid tissue neoplasm"},{"code":"111301","display":"Axillary nodal metastases","definition":"Metastatic disease to the axillary node"},{"extension":[{"url":"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/codesystem-replacedby","valueCoding":{"system":"http://hl7.org/fhir/sid/srt","code":"M-91203","display":"Angiosarcoma"}}],"code":"111302","display":"Angiosarcoma","definition":"A malignant neoplasm occurring most often in breast and skin, believed to originate from endothelial cells of blood vessels, microscopically composed of closely packed round or spindle shaped cells, some of which line small spaces resembling vascular clefts","property":[{"code":"status","valueCode":"deprecated"}]},{"code":"111303","display":"Blood vessel (vascular) invasion","definition":"Histological changes to the vascular system related to an invasive process"},{"code":"111304","display":"Carcinoma in children","definition":"Carcinoma of the breast found in patients less than 20 years of age"},{"code":"111305","display":"Carcinoma in ectopic breast","definition":"A carcinoma found in supernumerary breasts and aberrant breast tissue"},{"code":"111306","display":"Carcinoma with endocrine differentiation","definition":"A carcinoma that synthesizes substances, including hormones, not considered to be normal products of the breast"},{"code":"111307","display":"Basal cell carcinoma of nipple","definition":"A basal cell carcinoma that arises in the nipple of the breast"},{"extension":[{"url":"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/codesystem-replacedby","valueCoding":{"system":"http://hl7.org/fhir/sid/srt","code":"M-85733","display":"Carcinoma with metaplasia"}}],"code":"111308","display":"Carcinoma with metaplasia","definition":"Metaplastic carcinoma is cancer that begins in cells that have changed into another cell type (for example, a squamous cell of the esophagus changing to resemble a cell of the stomach). In some cases, metaplastic changes alone may mean there is an increased chance of cancer developing at the site. Metaplastic carcinoma is a relatively uncommon type of cancer with treatment generally similar to that of invasive ductal carcinoma of no special type.[1] FROM: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metaplastic_carcinoma","property":[{"code":"status","valueCode":"deprecated"}]},{"code":"111309","display":"Cartilaginous and osseous change","definition":"Tissue changes to bones and cartilage"},{"code":"111310","display":"Carcinoma in pregnancy and lactation","definition":"Carcinoma of the breast presenting during pregnancy or lactation"},{"extension":[{"url":"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/codesystem-replacedby","valueCoding":{"system":"http://hl7.org/fhir/sid/srt","code":"M-89803","display":"Carcinosarcoma"}}],"code":"111311","display":"Carcinosarcoma","definition":"A malignant neoplasm that contains elements of carcinoma and sarcoma, so extensively intermixed as to indicate neoplasia of epithelial and mesenchymal tissue","property":[{"code":"status","valueCode":"deprecated"}]},{"code":"111312","display":"Intraductal comedocarcinoma with necrosis","definition":"Comedocarcinoma of a duct with areas of necrotic tissue"},{"code":"111313","display":"Intraductal carcinoma, low grade","definition":"A non-invasive carcinoma restricted to the glandular lumen characterized by less aggressive malignant cytologic features and behavior"},{"extension":[{"url":"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/codesystem-replacedby","valueCoding":{"system":"http://hl7.org/fhir/sid/srt","code":"M-85072","display":"Intraductal carcinoma micro-papillary"}}],"code":"111314","display":"Intraductal carcinoma micro-papillary","definition":"Papillary and micropapillary Ductal Carcinoma In Situ (DCIS): the cancer cells arrange themselves in a fern-like pattern within the affected breast ducts; micropapillary DCIS cells are smaller than papillary DCIS cells. FROM: http://www.imaginis.com/breast-cancer-diagnosis/ductal-carcinoma-in-situ-dcis-3","property":[{"code":"status","valueCode":"deprecated"}]},{"code":"111315","display":"Intracystic papillary carcinoma","definition":"A malignant neoplasm characterized by the formation of numerous, irregular, finger-like projections of fibrous stroma that is covered with a surface layer of neoplastic epithelial cells found in a cyst"},{"code":"111316","display":"Invasive and in-situ carcinoma","definition":"Carcinoma with both characteristics of localized and spreading disease"},{"extension":[{"url":"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/codesystem-replacedby","valueCoding":{"system":"http://hl7.org/fhir/sid/srt","code":"M-85203","display":"Invasive lobular carcinoma"}}],"code":"111317","display":"Invasive lobular carcinoma","definition":"Invasive lobular carcinoma is a type of breast cancer that begins in the milk-producing glands (lobules) of the breast. Invasive cancer means the cancer cells have broken out of the lobule where they began and have the potential to spread to the lymph nodes and other areas of the body. Invasive lobular carcinoma typically doesn't form a lump, which is common in breast cancer. Instead, there is a change in the breast that feels like a thickening or fullness in one part of the breast and is different from the surrounding breast tissue. FROM: http://www.mayoclinic.org/diseases-conditions/invasive-lobular-carcinoma/basics/definition/con-20033968","property":[{"code":"status","valueCode":"deprecated"}]},{"code":"111318","display":"Leukemic infiltration","definition":"Mammary infiltrates as a secondary manifestation in patients with established leukemia"},{"code":"111320","display":"Lympathic vessel invasion","definition":"Histological changes to the lymphatic system related to an invasive process"},{"extension":[{"url":"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/codesystem-replacedby","valueCoding":{"system":"http://hl7.org/fhir/sid/srt","code":"M-95903","display":"Lymphoma"}}],"code":"111321","display":"Lymphoma","definition":"A heterogeneous group of neoplasms arising in the reticuloendoethelial and lymphatic systems","property":[{"code":"status","valueCode":"deprecated"}]},{"code":"111322","display":"Occult carcinoma presenting with axillary lymph node metastases","definition":"A small carcinoma, either asymptomatic or giving rise to metastases without symptoms due to the primary carcinoma presenting with metastatic disease in the axillary lymph nodes"},{"code":"111323","display":"Metastatic cancer to the breast","definition":"A malignant lesion in the breast with morphologic patterns not typical of breast carcinoma arising from a non-mammary malignant neoplasm"},{"code":"111324","display":"Metastatic cancer to the breast from the colon","definition":"A malignant lesion in the breast with morphologic patterns not typical of breast carcinoma arising from a neoplasm in the colon"},{"code":"111325","display":"Metastatic cancer to the breast from the lung","definition":"A malignant lesion in the breast with morphologic patterns not typical of breast carcinoma arising from a neoplasm in the lung"},{"code":"111326","display":"Metastatic melanoma to the breast","definition":"A malignant lesion in the breast with morphologic patterns not typical of breast carcinoma arising from a melanoma"},{"code":"111327","display":"Metastatic cancer to the breast from the ovary","definition":"A malignant lesion in the breast with morphologic patterns not typical of breast carcinoma arising from a neoplasm in the ovary"},{"code":"111328","display":"Metastatic sarcoma to the breast","definition":"A malignant lesion in the breast with morphologic patterns not typical of breast carcinoma arising from a sarcoma"},{"code":"111329","display":"Multifocal intraductal carcinoma","definition":"Multiple foci of non-invasive carcinoma restricted to the glandular lumen"},{"code":"111330","display":"Metastatic disease to axillary node","definition":"A malignant lesion in an axillary node arising from a non-axillary neoplasm"},{"extension":[{"url":"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/codesystem-replacedby","valueCoding":{"system":"http://hl7.org/fhir/sid/srt","code":"M-88303","display":"Malignant fibrous histiocytoma"}}],"code":"111331","display":"Malignant fibrous histiocytoma","definition":"Pleomorphic undifferentiated sarcoma (abbreviated PUS), also undifferentiated pleomorphic sarcoma and previously malignant fibrous histiocytoma (abbreviated MFH), is a type of soft tissue sarcoma. FROM: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pleomorphic_undifferentiated_sarcoma","property":[{"code":"status","valueCode":"deprecated"}]},{"code":"111332","display":"Multifocal invasive ductal carcinoma","definition":"Multiple sites of ductal carcinoma"},{"code":"111333","display":"Metastasis to an intramammary lymph node","definition":"A malignant lesion in a intramammary lymph node arising from a non-intramammary lymph node neoplasm"},{"code":"111334","display":"Malignant melanoma of nipple","definition":"A malignant melanoma of the skin that arises in the nipple of the breast"},{"extension":[{"url":"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/codesystem-replacedby","valueCoding":{"system":"http://hl7.org/fhir/sid/srt","code":"D0-F035F","display":"Neoplasm of the mammary skin"}}],"code":"111335","display":"Neoplasm of the mammary skin","property":[{"code":"status","valueCode":"deprecated"}]},{"extension":[{"url":"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/codesystem-replacedby","valueCoding":{"system":"http://hl7.org/fhir/sid/srt","code":"M-80502","display":"Papillary carcinoma in-situ"}}],"code":"111336","display":"Papillary carcinoma in-situ","definition":"Papillary and micropapillary Ductal Carcinoma In Situ (DCIS): the cancer cells arrange themselves in a fern-like pattern within the affected breast ducts; micropapillary DCIS cells are smaller than papillary DCIS cells. FROM: http://www.imaginis.com/breast-cancer-diagnosis/ductal-carcinoma-in-situ-dcis-3","property":[{"code":"status","valueCode":"deprecated"}]},{"code":"111338","display":"Recurrent malignancy","definition":"Recurrent malignancy"},{"code":"111340","display":"Squamous cell carcinoma of the nipple","definition":"Squamous cell carcinoma to the terminal portion of the alveolar"},{"code":"111341","display":"Intraductal carcinoma, high grade","definition":"A non-invasive carcinoma restricted to the glandular lumen characterized by more aggressive malignant cytologic features and behavior"},{"extension":[{"url":"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/codesystem-replacedby","valueCoding":{"system":"http://hl7.org/fhir/sid/srt","code":"M-82013","display":"Invasive cribriform carcinoma"}}],"code":"111342","display":"Invasive cribriform carcinoma","definition":"Invasive tumor with cribriform pattern similar to cribriform DCIS. Low grade, cribriform appearance (well defined spaces formed by arches of cells) similar to cribriform DCIS but with larger cells, more cytoplasm and more vesicular nuclei: Tumor cells are small, often have apical snouts, mild/moderate nuclear pleomorphism; Also stromal invasion by islands of cells, often angulated; May have predominantly solid appearance; Associated with cribriform DCIS; Often mixed with tubular carcinoma. FROM: http://www.pathologyoutlines.com/topic/breastmalignantcribriform.html","property":[{"code":"status","valueCode":"deprecated"}]},{"code":"111343","display":"Angular margins","definition":"An indication that some or all of the margin of a lesion has sharp corners, often forming acute angles"},{"code":"111344","display":"Fine pleomorphic calcification","definition":"Calcifications that vary in sizes and shapes and are usually smaller than0.5 mm in diameter"},{"code":"111345","display":"Macrocalcifications","definition":"Coarse calcifications that are 0.5 mm or greater in size"},{"code":"111346","display":"Calcifications within a mass","definition":"An indicator that calcifications are imbedded within a mass"},{"code":"111347","display":"Calcifications outside of a mass","definition":"An indicator that calcifications are imaged outside of a mass finding"},{"code":"111350","display":"Breast background echotexture","definition":"Tissue composition of the breast noted on sonography"},{"code":"111351","display":"Homogeneous fat echotexture","definition":"Fat lobules and uniformly echogenic bands of supporting structures comprise the bulk of breast tissue"},{"code":"111352","display":"Homogeneous fibroglandular echotexture","definition":"A uniformly echogenic layer of fibroglandular tissue is seen beneath a thin layer of subcutaneous fat"},{"code":"111353","display":"Heterogeneous echotexture","definition":"The breast texture is characterized by multiple small areas of increased and decreased echogenicity"},{"code":"111354","display":"Orientation","definition":"Referential relationship of the finding to the imaging device as noted on sonography"},{"code":"111355","display":"Parallel","definition":"The long axis of a lesion parallels the skin line (\"wider-than-tall\" or in a horizontal orientation)"},{"code":"111356","display":"Not parallel","definition":"The anterior-posterior or vertical dimension is greater than the transverse or horizontal dimension"},{"code":"111357","display":"Lesion boundary","definition":"The lesion boundary describes the transition zone between themas and the surrounding tissue"},{"code":"111358","display":"Abrupt interface","definition":"The sharp demarcation between the lesion and surrounding tissue can be imperceptible or a distinct well-defined echogenic rim of any thickness"},{"code":"111359","display":"Echogenic halo","definition":"There is no sharp demarcation between the mass and the surrounding tissue, which is bridged by an echogenic transition zone"},{"code":"111360","display":"Echo pattern","definition":"An imaging characteristic of resonance noted during sonography"},{"code":"111361","display":"Anechoic","definition":"Without internal echoes"},{"code":"111362","display":"Hyperechoic","definition":"Having increased echogenicity relative to fat or equal to fibroglandular tissue"},{"code":"111363","display":"Complex","definition":"Mass contains both anechoic and echogenic components"},{"code":"111364","display":"Hypoechoic","definition":"Defined relative to fat; masses are characterized by low-level echoes throughout; e.g. appearance of a complicated cyst or fibroadenoma"},{"code":"111365","display":"Isoechoic","definition":"Having the same echogenicity as fat (a complicated cyst or fibroadenoma may be isoechoic or hypoechoic)"},{"code":"111366","display":"Posterior acoustic features","definition":"The attenuation characteristics of a mass with respect to its acoustic transmission"},{"code":"111367","display":"No posterior acoustic features","definition":"No posterior shadowing or enhancement"},{"code":"111368","display":"Posterior enhancement","definition":"Increased posterior echoes"},{"code":"111369","display":"Posterior shadowing","definition":"Decreased posterior echoes; edge shadows are excluded"},{"code":"111370","display":"Combined posterior enhancement and shadowing","definition":"More than one pattern of posterior attenuation, both shadowing and enhancement"},{"code":"111371","display":"Identifiable effect on surrounding tissues","definition":"Sonographic appearance of adjacent structures relative to a mass finding"},{"code":"111372","display":"Vascularity","definition":"Characterization of vascularization in region of interest"},{"code":"111373","display":"Vascularity not present","definition":"Vascularity not evident, such as on ultrasound"},{"code":"111374","display":"Vascularity not assessed","definition":"Vascularity not evaluated"},{"code":"111375","display":"Vascularity present in lesion","definition":"Vascularity on imaging is seen within a lesion"},{"code":"111376","display":"Vascularity present immediately adjacent to lesion","definition":"Vascularity on imaging is seen immediately adjacent to a lesion"},{"code":"111377","display":"Diffusely increased vascularity in surrounding tissue","definition":"Vascularity on imaging is considered diffusely elevated within the surrounding breast tissue"},{"code":"111380","display":"Correlation to other Findings","definition":"Relationship of the new anomaly to other clinical or imaging anomalies"},{"code":"111381","display":"Correlates to physical exam findings","definition":"An indication that the current imaging finding relates to a finding from a clinical breast exam"},{"code":"111382","display":"Correlates to mammography findings","definition":"An indication that the current imaging finding relates to a finding from a mammography exam"},{"code":"111383","display":"Correlates to MRI findings","definition":"An indication that the current imaging finding relates to a finding from a breast MRI exam"},{"code":"111384","display":"Correlates to ultrasound findings","definition":"An indication that the current imaging finding relates to a finding from a breast ultrasound exam"},{"code":"111385","display":"Correlates to other imaging findings","definition":"An indication that the current imaging finding relates to a finding from an imaging exam"},{"code":"111386","display":"No correlation to other imaging findings","definition":"An indication that the current imaging finding has no relation to findings from any other imaging exam"},{"code":"111387","display":"No correlation to clinical findings","definition":"An indication that the current imaging finding has no relation to any other clinical findings"},{"code":"111388","display":"Malignancy Type","definition":"Classification of the cancer as invasive, DCIS, or other"},{"code":"111389","display":"Invasive breast carcinoma","definition":"A malignancy that has spread beyond an area of focus"},{"code":"111390","display":"Other malignancy type","definition":"A breast cancer with malignant pathology findings that are not classified as invasive or in situ"},{"code":"111391","display":"Menstrual Cycle Phase","definition":"A specific timeframe during menses"},{"code":"111392","display":"1st week","definition":"In the first week of the menstrual cycle phase, that is, one week following menses"},{"code":"111393","display":"2nd week","definition":"In the second week of the menstrual cycle phase, that is, two weeks following menses"},{"code":"111394","display":"3rd week","definition":"In the third week of the menstrual cycle phase, that is, three weeks following menses"},{"code":"111395","display":"Estimated Timeframe","definition":"An estimated period of time"},{"code":"111396","display":"< 3 months ago","definition":"An event occurred less than 3 months ago"},{"code":"111397","display":"4 months to 1 year ago","definition":"An event occurred between 4 months and 1 year ago"},{"code":"111398","display":"> 1 year ago","definition":"An event occurred longer than 1 year ago"},{"code":"111399","display":"Timeframe uncertain","definition":"The timing of an event is not recalled"},{"code":"111400","display":"Breast Imaging Report","definition":"Report title for the diagnostic report for one or more breast imaging or intervention procedures"},{"code":"111401","display":"Reason for procedure","definition":"Concept name for the description of why a procedure has been performed"},{"code":"111402","display":"Clinical Finding","definition":"A finding during clinical examination (i.e., history and physical examination) such as pain, palpable mass or discharge"},{"code":"111403","display":"Baseline screening mammogram","definition":"First screening mammogram taken for patient that is used as a comparison baseline for further examinations"},{"code":"111404","display":"First mammogram ever","definition":"First mammogram taken for a patient without regard to whether it was for screening or a diagnostic procedure"},{"code":"111405","display":"Implant type","definition":"Concept name for the material of which a breast prosthetic device is constructed"},{"code":"111406","display":"Number of similar findings","definition":"A numeric count of findings classified as similar in nature"},{"code":"111407","display":"Implant finding","definition":"Concept name for the status of a breast prosthetic device as noted by imaging"},{"code":"111408","display":"Film Screen Mammography","definition":"Mammogram using traditional X-Ray film"},{"code":"111409","display":"Digital Mammography","definition":"Mammogram using a digital image acquisition system"},{"code":"111410","display":"Surgical consult","definition":"Referred for evaluation by a surgeon"},{"code":"111411","display":"Mammography CAD","definition":"Computer aided detection and/or computer aided diagnosis for mammography"},{"code":"111412","display":"Narrative Summary","definition":"Concept name for a text-based section of a report"},{"code":"111413","display":"Overall Assessment","definition":"A title for a report section that summarizes all interpretation results for a report with one overriding assessment; e.g. benign or negative"},{"code":"111414","display":"Supplementary Data","definition":"Concept name for a collection of supporting evidence for a report"},{"code":"111415","display":"Additional evaluation requested from prior study","definition":"Prior study indicates that additional imaging be performed to further evaluate a suspicious or questionable anatomic region"},{"code":"111416","display":"Follow-up at short interval from prior study","definition":"The prior study recommended a follow-up breast imaging exam in 1 to 11 months (generally in 6 months)"},{"code":"111417","display":"History of breast augmentation, asymptomatic","definition":"Prior breast augmentation (breast enlargement) and is not presenting with any symptoms"},{"code":"111418","display":"Review of an outside study","definition":"Review or second opinion made on an image performed outside of the facility"},{"code":"111419","display":"Additional evaluation requested from abnormal screening exam","definition":"Additional breast imaging performed at the time of the patient's screening mammogram"},{"code":"111420","display":"History of benign breast biopsy","definition":"Patient has had previous benign breast biopsies"},{"code":"111421","display":"Personal history of breast cancer with breast conservation therapy","definition":"Patient has had a prior surgery such as a lumpectomy or quadrantectomy to remove malignant breast tissue, but breast tissue remains"},{"code":"111423","display":"Physical Examination Results","definition":"The results of a physical examination performed on the patient, possibly including the results of inspection, palpation, auscultation, or percussion"},{"code":"111424","display":"Comparison to previous findings","definition":"The result of assessing the current imaging exam in comparison to previous imaging exams"},{"code":"111425","display":"Intraluminal filling defect","definition":"An abnormality observed during ductography where the ductal system within the breast fills in an abnormal pattern. Ductography is an imaging exam in which a radio opaque contrast media is introduced into the ductal system of the breast through the nipple and images of the ductal system are obtained"},{"code":"111426","display":"Multiple filling defect","definition":"During ductography an observation of more than one filling abnormality within the breast ductal system"},{"code":"111427","display":"Abrupt duct termination","definition":"An abnormality observed during ductography where the ductal system within the breast terminates in an unusual fashion"},{"code":"111428","display":"Extravasation","definition":"Abnormal flowage of contrast media within the breast noted on ductography"},{"code":"111429","display":"Duct narrowing","definition":"An abnormality observed during ductography where the ductal system within the breast appears narrow"},{"code":"111430","display":"Cyst fill","definition":"During ductography an observation of the contrast media filling a cyst within the breast"},{"code":"111431","display":"Instrument Approach","definition":"The area and line within the anatomy through which a needle or instrument passes during an interventional procedure"},{"code":"111432","display":"Inferolateral to superomedial","definition":"The line within the anatomy from the lower outer to the upper inner aspect; e.g. through which a needle or instrument passes in an interventional procedure"},{"code":"111433","display":"Inferomedial to superolateral","definition":"The line within the anatomy from the lower inner to the upper outer aspect; e.g. through which a needle or instrument passes in an interventional procedure"},{"code":"111434","display":"Superolateral to inferomedial","definition":"The line within the anatomy from the upper outer to the lower inner aspect; e.g. through which a needle or instrument passes in an interventional procedure"},{"code":"111435","display":"Superomedial to inferolateral","definition":"The line within the anatomy from the upper inner to the lower outer aspect; e.g. through which a needle or instrument passes in an interventional procedure"},{"code":"111436","display":"Number of passes","definition":"The number of times a biopsy instrument is passed through an area of interest"},{"code":"111437","display":"Number of specimens","definition":"The number of biopsy specimens obtained from an interventional procedure"},{"code":"111438","display":"Needle in target","definition":"An indicator of whether or not a biopsy or localizing needle in an interventional procedure is seen to be in the area of interest"},{"code":"111439","display":"Number of needles around target","definition":"The number of localizing needles placed around the area of interest in an interventional procedure"},{"code":"111440","display":"Incision made","definition":"An indicator of whether or not an incision was made in the anatomy during an interventional procedure"},{"extension":[{"url":"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/codesystem-replacedby","valueCoding":{"system":"http://dicom.nema.org/resources/ontology/DCM","code":"111123","display":"Marker placement"}}],"code":"111441","display":"Microclip placed","definition":"An indicator of whether or not a radio opaque microclip was placed in the anatomy during an interventional procedure","property":[{"code":"status","valueCode":"deprecated"}]},{"code":"111442","display":"Confirmation of target","definition":"An indicator of the degree of success of an interventional procedure"},{"code":"111443","display":"Target completely contained in the specimen","definition":"An indicator that during an interventional procedure the area of interest was fully excised and is noted in the resultant biopsy specimen"},{"code":"111444","display":"Target partially obtained in the specimen","definition":"An indicator that during an interventional procedure the area of interest was partially excised and is noted in the resultant biopsy specimen"},{"code":"111445","display":"Target not in the specimen","definition":"An indicator that following an interventional procedure the area of interest is not seen in the resultant biopsy specimen"},{"code":"111446","display":"Calcifications seen in the core","definition":"An indicator that following an interventional procedure the targeted calcifications are noted in the resultant biopsy specimen"},{"code":"111447","display":"Lesion completely removed","definition":"An indicator that during an interventional procedure the area of interest was fully excised and is noted in the resultant biopsy specimen"},{"code":"111448","display":"Lesion partially removed","definition":"An indicator that during an interventional procedure the area of interest was partially excised and is noted in the resultant biopsy specimen"},{"code":"111449","display":"Fluid obtained","definition":"An indicator that during an interventional procedure fluid was successfully aspirated"},{"code":"111450","display":"Light brown color","definition":"Color that is a light shade of brown"},{"code":"111451","display":"Dark red color","definition":"Color that is a dark shade of red"},{"code":"111452","display":"Dark brown color","definition":"Color that is a dark shade of brown"},{"code":"111453","display":"Bright red color","definition":"Color that is a bright shade of red"},{"code":"111454","display":"Blood tinged color","definition":"Color that is tinged with the color of blood"},{"code":"111455","display":"Occult blood test result","definition":"An indicator of whether or not the fluid obtained during an interventional procedure contains red blood cells"},{"code":"111456","display":"Action on fluid","definition":"An indicator of whether or not fluid during an interventional procedure was sent for cytological analysis or simply discarded"},{"code":"111457","display":"Sent for analysis","definition":"An indicator that fluid obtained during an interventional procedure was sent to a laboratory for analysis"},{"code":"111458","display":"Discarded","definition":"An indicator that fluid obtained during an interventional procedure was discarded"},{"code":"111459","display":"Mass with calcifications","definition":"A radiopaque density noted during diagnostic imaging that has associated calcific densities"},{"code":"11146