nned for translation"},{"code":"112379","display":"Degree of Freedom Exact Rotational Translation Value","definition":"Defines the exact value that was planned for rotation"},{"code":"112380","display":"Degree of Freedom Minimum Rotational Value","definition":"Defines the minimum value that was planned for rotation"},{"code":"112381","display":"Degree of Freedom Maximum Rotational Value","definition":"Defines the maximum value that was planned for rotation"},{"code":"112700","display":"Peri-operative Photographic Imaging","definition":"Procedure step protocol for photographic imaging of surgical procedures, including photography of specimens collected"},{"code":"112701","display":"Gross Specimen Imaging","definition":"Procedure step protocol for imaging gross specimens, typically with a photographic camera (modality XC), and planning further dissection"},{"code":"112702","display":"Slide Microscopy","definition":"Procedure step protocol for imaging slide specimens"},{"code":"112703","display":"Whole Slide Imaging","definition":"Procedure step protocol for imaging slide specimens using a whole slide scanner"},{"code":"112704","display":"WSI 20X RGB","definition":"Procedure step protocol for imaging slide specimens using a whole slide scanner with a 20X nominal objective lens, in full color, with a single imaging focal plane across the image"},{"code":"112705","display":"WSI 40X RGB","definition":"Procedure step protocol for imaging slide specimens using a whole slide scanner with a 40X nominal objective lens, in full color, with a single imaging focal plane across the image"},{"code":"112706","display":"Illumination Method","definition":"Technique of illuminating specimen"},{"code":"112707","display":"Number of focal planes","definition":"Number of focal planes for a microscopy image acquisition"},{"code":"112708","display":"Focal plane Z offset","definition":"Nominal distance above a reference plane (typically a slide glass substrate top surface) of the focal plane"},{"code":"112709","display":"Magnification selection","definition":"Microscope magnification based on nominal objective lens power"},{"code":"112710","display":"Illumination wavelength","definition":"Nominal center wavelength for an imaging spectral band"},{"code":"112711","display":"Illumination spectral band","definition":"Name (coded) for an imaging spectral band"},{"code":"112712","display":"Optical filter type","definition":"Type of filter inserted into the optical imaging path"},{"code":"112713","display":"Tissue selection method","definition":"Technique for identifying tissue to be imaged versus area of slide not to be imaged"},{"code":"112714","display":"Multiple planes","definition":"Imaging performed at multiple imaging (focal) planes"},{"code":"112715","display":"5X","definition":"Nominal 5 power objective lens, resulting in a digital image at approximately 2 um/pixel spacing"},{"code":"112716","display":"10X","definition":"Nominal 10 power objective lens, resulting in a digital image at approximately 1 um/pixel spacing"},{"code":"112717","display":"20X","definition":"Nominal 20 power microscope objective lens, resulting in a digital image at approximately 0.5 um/pixel spacing"},{"code":"112718","display":"40X","definition":"Nominal 40 power microscope objective lens, with a combined condenser and objective lens numerical aperture of approximately 1.3, resulting in a digital image at approximately 0.25 um/pixel spacing"},{"code":"112719","display":"Nominal empty tile suppression","definition":"Equipment-specific nominal or default method for identifying tiles without tissue imaged for suppression from inclusion in image object"},{"code":"112720","display":"High threshold empty tile suppression","definition":"Equipment-specific high threshold method for identifying tiles without tissue imaged for suppression from inclusion in image object"},{"code":"112721","display":"No empty tile suppression","definition":"Tiles without tissue imaged are not suppressed from inclusion in image object"},{"code":"113000","display":"Of Interest","definition":"Of Interest"},{"code":"113001","display":"Rejected for Quality Reasons","definition":"Rejected for Quality Reasons"},{"code":"113002","display":"For Referring Provider","definition":"For Referring Provider"},{"code":"113003","display":"For Surgery","definition":"For Surgery"},{"code":"113004","display":"For Teaching","definition":"For Teaching"},{"code":"113005","display":"For Conference","definition":"For Conference"},{"code":"113006","display":"For Therapy","definition":"For Therapy"},{"code":"113007","display":"For Patient","definition":"For Patient"},{"code":"113008","display":"For Peer Review","definition":"For Peer Review"},{"code":"113009","display":"For Research","definition":"For Research"},{"code":"113010","display":"Quality Issue","definition":"Quality Issue"},{"code":"113011","display":"Document Title Modifier","definition":"Document Title Modifier"},{"code":"113012","display":"Key Object Description","definition":"Key Object Description"},{"code":"113013","display":"Best In Set","definition":"A selection that represents the \"best\" chosen from a larger set of items; e.g. the best images within a Study or Series. The criteria against which \"best\" is measured is not defined. Contrast this with the more specific term \"Best illustration of finding\""},{"code":"113014","display":"Study","definition":"A study is a collection of one or more series of medical images, presentation states, and/or SR documents that are logically related for the purpose of diagnosing a patient. A study may include composite instances that are created by a single modality, multiple modalities or by multiple devices of the same modality. [From Section A.1.2.2 \"Study IE\" in PS3.3 ]"},{"code":"113015","display":"Series","definition":"A distinct logical set used to group composite instances. All instances within a Series are of the same modality, in the same Frame of Reference (if any), and created by the same equipment. [See Section A.1.2.3 \"Series IE\" in PS3.3 ]"},{"code":"113016","display":"Performed Procedure Step","definition":"An arbitrarily defined unit of service that has actually been performed (not just scheduled). [From Section 7.3.1.9 \"Modality Performed Procedure Step\" in PS3.3 ]"},{"code":"113017","display":"Stage-View","definition":"An image or set of images illustrating a specific stage (phase in a stress echo exam protocol) and view (combination of the transducer position and orientation at the time of image acquisition)"},{"code":"113018","display":"For Printing","definition":"For Printing"},{"code":"113020","display":"For Report Attachment","definition":"Selection of information objects for attachment to the clinical report of the Current Requested Procedure"},{"code":"113021","display":"For Litigation","definition":"List of objects that are related to litigation and should be specially handled; e.g. may apply if a complaint has been received regarding a patient, or a specific set of images has been the subject of a subpoena, and needs to be sequestered or excluded from automatic purging according to retention policy"},{"code":"113026","display":"Double exposure","definition":"Double exposure"},{"code":"113030","display":"Manifest","definition":"A list of objects that have been exported out of one organizational domain into another domain. Typically, the first domain has no direct control over what the second domain will do with the objects"},{"code":"113031","display":"Signed Manifest","definition":"A signed list of objects that have been exported out of one organizational domain into another domain, referenced securely with either Digital Signatures or MACs. Typically, the first domain has no direct control over what the second domain will do with the objects"},{"code":"113032","display":"Complete Study Content","definition":"The list of objects that constitute a study at the time that the list was created"},{"code":"113033","display":"Signed Complete Study Content","definition":"The signed list of objects that constitute a study at the time that the list was created, referenced securely with either Digital Signatures or MACs"},{"code":"113034","display":"Complete Acquisition Content","definition":"The list of objects that were generated in a single procedure step"},{"code":"113035","display":"Signed Complete Acquisition Content","definition":"The signed list of objects that were generated in a single procedure step, referenced securely with either Digital Signatures or MACs"},{"code":"113036","display":"Group of Frames for Display","definition":"A list of frames or single-frame or entire multi-frame instances that together constitute a set for some purpose, such as might be displayed together in the same viewport, as distinct from another set that might be displayed in a separate viewport"},{"code":"113037","display":"Rejected for Patient Safety Reasons","definition":"List of objects whose use is potentially harmful to the patient; e.g. an improperly labeled image could lead to dangerous surgical decisions"},{"code":"113038","display":"Incorrect Modality Worklist Entry","definition":"List of objects that were acquired using an incorrect modality worklist entry, and that should not be used, since they may be incorrectly identified"},{"code":"113039","display":"Data Retention Policy Expired","definition":"List of objects that have expired according to a defined data retention policy"},{"code":"113040","display":"Lossy Compression","definition":"Lossy compression has been applied to an image"},{"code":"113041","display":"Apparent Diffusion Coefficient","definition":"Values are derived by calculation of the apparent diffusion coefficient"},{"code":"113042","display":"Pixel by pixel addition","definition":"Values are derived by the pixel by pixel addition of two images"},{"code":"113043","display":"Diffusion weighted","definition":"Values are derived by calculation of the diffusion weighting"},{