e for the integrated dose meter or dose calculation"},{"code":"113724","display":"Calibration Responsible Party","definition":"Individual or organization responsible for calibration"},{"code":"113725","display":"Dose (RP) Total","definition":"Total Dose related to Reference Point (RP). (in the scope of the including report)"},{"code":"113726","display":"Fluoro Dose Area Product Total","definition":"Total calculated Dose Area Product applied in Fluoroscopy Modes (in the scope of the including report)"},{"code":"113727","display":"Acquisition Dose Area Product Total","definition":"Total calculated Dose Area Product applied in Acquisition Modes (in the scope of the including report)"},{"code":"113728","display":"Fluoro Dose (RP) Total","definition":"Dose applied in Fluoroscopy Modes, related to Reference Point (RP). (in the scope of the including report)"},{"code":"113729","display":"Acquisition Dose (RP) Total","definition":"Dose applied in Acquisition Modes, related to Reference Point (RP). (in the scope of the including report)"},{"code":"113730","display":"Total Fluoro Time","definition":"Total accumulated clock time of Fluoroscopy in the scope of the including report (i.e., the sum of the Irradiation Duration values for accumulated fluoroscopy irradiation events)"},{"code":"113731","display":"Total Number of Radiographic Frames","definition":"Accumulated Count of exposure pulses (single or multi-frame encoded) created from irradiation events performed with high dose (acquisition)"},{"code":"113732","display":"Fluoro Mode","definition":"Mode of application of X-Rays during Fluoroscopy"},{"code":"113733","display":"KVP","definition":"Applied X-Ray Tube voltage at peak of X-Ray generation, in kilovolts; Mean value if measured over multiple peaks (pulses)"},{"code":"113734","display":"X-Ray Tube Current","definition":"Mean value of applied Tube Current"},{"extension":[{"url":"http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/codesystem-replacedby","valueCoding":{"system":"http: